        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 7:49AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 749 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Mexico to near Swayzee.
Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Marion, Peru, Wabash, North Manchester, Gas City, Jonesboro,
Sweetser, Swayzee, Bunker Hill, La Fontaine, Mexico, Wells, Sims,
Converse, Erie, Roann, Lagro, Amboy, Richvalley, and Landess.

This includes Interstate 69 in Indiana between mile markers 262 and
267.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
